column21: Span is how far a simulant randomly moves in one step
How far a simulant searches for a nearby shopping centre (etc..) to visit. Happens after moving.
How often a simulant searches for nearby shopping centres to visit.
The proportion of people that try (at all) to avoid others.
The proportion of time that people-avoiders try to avoid others.
PPA and PTA are set at the start of a stage and drop by 1% per day down to this bound.
Whether tracked cases are isolated as well as their household.
What proportion of the workforce is considered to be essential.
The proportion of people that always wear a mask (except when at home).
Whether the tracking system is in use.
This many people are randomly teleported halfway around the world each day.

column1: 75% of usual iso compliance for non-reported
Proportion of people who try to avoid contact with others (excluding their household)
Proportion of time spent trying to avoid contacts, for those that attempt to do so.
Complacency: Minimal value that restrictions above reduce to as a result of fatigue, at one percentage point per day after a stage is entered.
Essential workers: Proportion of working age adults classified as essential workers (not taking part in the contact avoiding system)
Schools open (disable contact avoiding behaviour among students)
Mask wearing: Proportion of people that wear masks outside the home.
Super spreaders: Proportion of people that engage in super spreading behaviour each day (move to a random gathering location)
Underlying frequency of visiting a random nearby gather location each day (supermarkets etc)
Radius for determining whether a gather location counts as nearby
Maximum daily speed in the simulation
